Bioinformatics is useful for handling large and complex biological data such as genome sequences. The basic methodology and core tools needed to tackle bioinformatics problems is common to many projects. This course will provide the introduction to the main tools used in the management and analysis of bioinformatics data (e.g. R) and explains how these can be used together to tackle the bioinformatics problems.
